(49, 'Doctors', 'doctors', '', '<span class="StaffNameText"><strong>Dr. Glenn M.  Charles, D.O.</strong>    <br />                   </span>                                                                         <img src="http://maximlrg.com/maximonline/pages/doctors_clip_image001.jpg" border="0" alt="http://www.charlesmedicalgroup.com/images/Dr_Charles_photo.jpg" hspace="5" width="176" height="156" align="right" /><br /> Cosmetic Surgeon/ Diplomat of the American Board of Cosmetic Surgery, Diplomat of the American Board of Anti-Aging Medicine Glenn M. Charles, D.O. specializes exclusively in the practice of cosmetic surgery including hair restoration surgery and Anti-Aging Medicine. Dr. Charles prides himself on his advanced knowledge in the art of all aspects of Anti-Aging and preventative medicine. <br />                     <br /> “We go beyond cosmetic compromises and look at the underlying causes of the problem in the first place. Age Management, at our center is the main focus. This is the unique difference with our process over others. Although me may not be able to stimulate the re-growth of your hair that has already fallen out, we certainly will work to make it thicker, more dense and prevent it in the future. It is truly complementary medicine.”<br />   <br /> Some of our new bio marker technologies include DNA markers that denote the aging process. DNA damage, is the underlying cause and leads to altered genetic expression, disease, and accelerated hair loss and basically, aging of humans. DNA serum protein thiol levels in blood are a direct measure of this process. We do these custom tests in the office to name a few. Besides incredible new science advancement in biomarker testing, Nutracuetical and Pharmaceutical protocols that influence the anabolic, restorative activity in the body and reduce the DNA catabolism, are fantastic options for the patient.<br />                     <br /> In addition, we have the diagnostic biomarkers that influence a comprehensive look at the body and its hormonal process that affects human deterioration. Panels, such as, Chemical Toxicity, Gastrointestinal and Parasite Panels that clinically affect the patient adversely may be reversed by implementing ‘cutting edge’ protocols that have been successful in disease and hair loss reversal. “Our clients <br />                     <br /> Dr. Charles acted as the primary physician trainer in hair restoration surgery for a large hair transplant organization from 1997-1999. Dr. Charles is active in several medical societies including, The International Society of Hair Restoration Surgery (ISHRS), The International Alliance of Hair Restoration Surgery (IAHRS), The International Society of Cosmetic Laser Surgeons, and The American Society of Laser Medicine and Surgery. The American College of Anti-Aging Medicine. <br />                     <br /> Dr. Charles regularly has articles published in the Hair Transplant Forum International and is a faculty lecturer at the ISHRS annual conference. <br /> Most recently he performed surgery at the World Hair Society annual live surgery workshop, one of the most prestigious invitations in the hair restoration industry internationally. He also is a member of the American Board of Hair Restoration Surgery Examination Committee, which oversees the industry standard practices.<br />                      <br />                     Dr. Charles  regularly lectures on Anti-Aging Medicine and cosmetic enhancement procedures.<br />                     He also is  listed in the Who''s Who of doctors in 2002. <br />                     <br />   <img src="http://maximlrg.com/maximonline/pages/doctors_clip_image002.jpg" border="0" alt="http://www.charlesmedicalgroup.com/images/Dr_Charles_interview.jpg" hspace="5" width="150" height="100" align="left" />Dr. Charles is a caring, gentle, honest, energetic doctor who empathizes with the patients hair alopecia or hair loss. He is truly dedicated to the restoration and the rejuvenation of the hair and the entire body. He is directly involved in every aspect of each surgery. Generally, because so much individual attention to detail is needed on each patient only 1 or 2 cases is performed per day. All grafts are placed with precise angulation and direction with an absolute perfectionist approach. Patients from all four corners of the globe come to Charles Medical Group new state of the art surgical Center to obtain natural/undetectable results. <br /> Glenn M. Charles was born in Buffalo, New York. He was raised in the suburbs of Detroit, Michigan. Dr. Charles received his undergraduate degree from Michigan State University. He obtained a medical degree from Nova Southeastern University School of medicine in North Miami Beach, Fl., followed by an internship and residency in Diagnostic Radiology at Michigan State University affiliated hospitals.', '', 1, 4, 0, 25, '2009-04-01 14:12:02', 62, '', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', 0, 0, '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '2009-04-01 14:12:02', '0000-00-00 00:00:00', '', '', 'show_title=\nlink_titles=\nshow_intro=\nshow_section=\nlink_section=\nshow_category=\nlink_category=\nshow_vote=\nshow_author=\nshow_create_date=\nshow_modify_date=\nshow_pdf_icon=\nshow_print_icon=\nshow_email_icon=\nlanguage=\nkeyref=\nreadmore=', 1, 0, 42, '', '', 0, 427, 'robots=\nauthor='),
